text: The hundred twenty-eighth note (also called a semihemidemisemiquaverRead, Gardner (1979). Music Notation, p.65. 2nd edition. Crescendo Taplinger. . or quasihemidemisemiquaver) is a note played for of the duration of a whole note which is where it gets its name.It has five flags or beams. In the \frac 4 4 time signature it has a value of of a beat. ==References== Category:Note values
title: Hundred twenty-eighth note
